    cn:
      "Documents were identified through referrals from organizations participating in the Evidence-Informed Healthcare Renewal Roundtable. Documents were deemed eligible for inclusion if they address or could inform healthcare renewal in Canada, which we defined as renewing, reforming or strengthening governance, financial and delivery arrangements within Canadian health systems (or said another way, the health system arrangements that get cost-effective programs, services and drugs to those who need them). Please note that the details for these documents on Health Systems Evidence are provided only in English and French.",
    es:
      "Documents were identified through referrals from organizations participating in the Evidence-Informed Healthcare Renewal Roundtable. Documents were deemed eligible for inclusion if they address or could inform healthcare renewal in Canada, which we defined as renewing, reforming or strengthening governance, financial and delivery arrangements within Canadian health systems (or said another way, the health system arrangements that get cost-effective programs, services and drugs to those who need them). Please note that the details for these documents on Health Systems Evidence are provided only in English and French.",
    pt:
      "Documents were identified through referrals from organizations participating in the Evidence-Informed Healthcare Renewal Roundtable. Documents were deemed eligible for inclusion if they address or could inform healthcare renewal in Canada, which we defined as renewing, reforming or strengthening governance, financial and delivery arrangements within Canadian health systems (or said another way, the health system arrangements that get cost-effective programs, services and drugs to those who need them). Please note that the details for these documents on Health Systems Evidence are provided only in English and French.",
    fr:
      "Les documents ont été identifiés grâce aux recommandations des organisations qui participent à la Table ronde sur le Renouvellement des soins de santé fondé sur des données probantes. Les documents étaient admissibles s’ils portaient sur, ou pouvaient éclairer, le renouvellement des soins de santé au Canada. De façon générale, cela signifie que les documents portaient sur des thèmes touchant le renouvellement, la réforme, ou le renforcement des arrangements de gouvernance, des arrangements financiers et des arrangements relatifs à la prestation de service dans les systèmes de santé au Canada (ou, dit autrement, les arrangements des systèmes de santé qui permettent de rendre accessible des programmes, services et médicaments efficients à ceux qui en ont besoin). Prenez note que les descriptions de ces documents sont seulement offertes en français et en anglais sur Health Systems Evidence.",
